name: Greater than
description: Compares 2 values to determine if the left value is strictly greater than the right value

name: Less than
description: Compares 2 values to determine if the left value is strictly less than the right value

name: Equal
description: Compares 2 values to determine if they are equal to each other

name: Not Equal
description: Compares 2 values to determine if they are not equal to each other

name: Greater than or equal
description: Compares 2 values to determine if the left value is greater than or equal to the right value

name: Less than or equal
description: Compares 2 values to determine if the left value is less than or equal to the right value

name: Plus
description: Adds 2 values together.  If the inputs are both numbers, + finds the sum.  If any of the inputs are strings, + concatenates them together.  If exactly 1 input is a string, the number is converted to a base-10 string such as "123".

name: Minus

unary.name: Negate
unary.description: Changes sign of the given number.  For example, -(3) evaluates to -3.

description: Calculates the left value minus the right number.  For example, 5 - 2 evaluates to 3.

name: Multiply
description: Multiplies the 2 numbers together.  In other words, * finds the product of 2 numbers.  For example, 2 * 5 evaluates to 10.

name: Divide
description: Divides the left value by the right value
